86
00:05:08,230 --> 00:05:09,859
It's unbelievable.

87
00:05:09,860 --> 00:05:12,390
It's amazing. Why didn't you tell me sooner?

88
00:05:12,390 --> 00:05:16,099
I didn't expect him to suddenly become the chairman of Poseidon overnight either.

89
00:05:16,099 --> 00:05:19,220
You two have been roommates for a while, and you didn't know that?

90
00:05:19,220 --> 00:05:21,280
He likes to keep things from me.

91
00:05:21,280 --> 00:05:23,289
If I knew he would become the chairman,

92
00:05:23,290 --> 00:05:25,640
would I have used your staff discount when I shopped?

93
00:05:25,640 --> 00:05:27,390
That's true.

94
00:05:27,390 --> 00:05:30,420
Are you guys having a fight now?

95
00:05:30,420 --> 00:05:33,009
He's probably playing me for a fool.

96
00:05:33,009 --> 00:05:35,530
First, he lets me live in an old Poseidon's warehouse.

97
00:05:35,530 --> 00:05:38,869
I was so grateful that I worked my butt off for him.

98
00:05:38,870 --> 00:05:41,790
Then he got me a job in the customer service team. Without any fuss,

99
00:05:41,790 --> 00:05:44,970
I tried my best to cover for him everyday.

100
00:05:44,970 --> 00:05:47,790
He must be laughing at me behind my back.

101
00:05:48,810 --> 00:05:51,139
I don't think Chairman is that kind of person.

102
00:05:51,139 --> 00:05:54,720
There must be a reason he's hiding his identity.

103
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:57,250
I'm a "reasonable" person too.

104
00:05:57,250 --> 00:05:59,769
Why didn't he tell me the "reason" then?

105
00:05:59,769 --> 00:06:03,120
Perhaps... he couldn't find a chance to tell you.

106
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:06,549
We used to stay together all the time, and he couldn't find a chance?

107
00:06:06,550 --> 00:06:08,750
Calm down and think.

108
00:06:08,750 --> 00:06:11,719
If our late Chairman hadn't passed away suddenly,

109
00:06:11,720 --> 00:06:15,170
he would've continued to train with you in Customer Service.

110
00:06:15,170 --> 00:06:18,979
- So?
- So... It's not that he didn't tell you.

111
00:06:18,979 --> 00:06:21,920
He directly brought you to Poseidon Department Store.

112
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:26,960
Are you saying that he used actions instead of words?

113
00:06:26,960 --> 00:06:31,730
Yes. The late Chairman passed away all of a sudden.

114
00:06:31,730 --> 00:06:35,060
The board members haven't accepted him since he's young

115
00:06:35,060 --> 00:06:37,330
and lacks experience.

116
00:06:37,330 --> 00:06:42,440
So at this time, you must support him.

117
00:06:42,440 --> 00:06:44,440
It sounds kind of reasonable.

118
00:06:44,440 --> 00:06:46,599
This is the "reason."

119
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:50,550
We can't imagine what he's going through at the moment.

120
00:06:50,550 --> 00:06:54,450
So, stop fighting with him.

121
00:06:54,450 --> 00:06:59,230
He must need you a lot now. You must support him.

122
00:07:08,580 --> 00:07:10,999
These are all his favorite dishes.

123
00:07:10,999 --> 00:07:13,200
It should be sincere enough.

124
00:07:18,310 --> 00:07:21,360
It's half past eight. Why isn't he home yet?

