288
00:20:58,070 --> 00:21:00,780
What are you doing?

289
00:21:03,590 --> 00:21:06,160
To prepare for the aftershocks later,

290
00:21:07,080 --> 00:21:09,559
I'll let you hold my hand while you sleep.

291
00:21:09,559 --> 00:21:11,579
Your hands are sweaty.

292
00:21:11,579 --> 00:21:14,590
That's dirty. That's your own sweat.

293
00:21:14,590 --> 00:21:17,780
♫ Constantly reminding ♫

294
00:21:17,780 --> 00:21:23,280
♫ Describing how powerless I am ♫

295
00:21:23,280 --> 00:21:27,180
♫ Just don’t be depressed, don’t be submissive ♫

296
00:21:27,180 --> 00:21:31,340
♫ Be courageous, but the memories fail me ♫

297
00:21:31,340 --> 00:21:33,600
♫ When mentioning you, I become powerless ♫

298
00:21:33,600 --> 00:21:37,730
♫ That word and sentence, I think of it but don’t say it ♫

299
00:21:37,730 --> 00:21:40,570
♫ Even the input method doesn’t forget ♫

300
00:21:40,570 --> 00:21:43,950
♫ How cruelly ask me to forget you? It’s you ♫

301
00:22:21,350 --> 00:22:25,630
♫ Day by day, I suddenly discover ♫

302
00:22:25,630 --> 00:22:30,740
♫ That strong but invisible line ♫

303
00:22:30,740 --> 00:22:35,000
♫ Lost in time ♫

304
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:39,360
♫ Foolishly unclear, pretends to be cool and loves to be jealous ♫

305
00:22:39,360 --> 00:22:44,430
♫ Then I discover the unbelievable change  ♫

306
00:22:44,430 --> 00:22:51,750
♫ I like to have you by my side ♫

307
00:22:52,420 --> 00:22:58,360
♫  I just want to be more than friends ♫

308
00:22:58,360 --> 00:23:03,600
♫ Why are we holding back? ♫

309
00:23:03,600 --> 00:23:06,110
♫ It’s not just a little bit ♫

310
00:23:06,110 --> 00:23:12,070
♫ I just want to be your boyfriend ♫

311
00:23:12,070 --> 00:23:17,280
♫ Give love a starting point ♫

312
00:23:17,280 --> 00:23:24,300
♫ This one-foot distance is a big adventure ♫

313
00:23:38,510 --> 00:23:40,899
The patient suffered a myocardial infarction. We couldn't save him.

314
00:23:40,900 --> 00:23:43,499
We tried our best. I'm sorry for your loss.

315
00:23:43,499 --> 00:23:46,949
Daddy, I thought you didn't want me anymore.

316
00:23:46,950 --> 00:23:50,690
Dad... How could you just leave like this?

317
00:23:50,690 --> 00:23:52,849
I have to leave.

318
00:23:52,850 --> 00:23:54,809
I have to go back to take care of my grandma.

319
00:23:54,810 --> 00:23:58,089
What if I leave one day, and you don't know how to do anything.

320
00:23:58,090 --> 00:24:00,300
How will you survive?

321
00:24:05,930 --> 00:24:08,779
Hi, Gorgeous.

322
00:24:08,779 --> 00:24:11,780
I'm Stacy. What's your name?

323
00:24:13,560 --> 00:24:15,880
Why are you ignoring me?

324
00:24:15,880 --> 00:24:17,950
Are you in a bad mood?

325
00:24:17,950 --> 00:24:20,870
It's okay. I'll drink with you.

326
00:24:21,870 --> 00:24:24,370
What are you drinking?

327
00:24:30,090 --> 00:24:33,190
Let us be friends. I'd like to propose a toast.

328
00:24:33,980 --> 00:24:36,280
Sorry... I didn't mean to.

329
00:24:36,280 --> 00:24:39,510
I didn't mean to. Let me clean it for you.

330
00:24:39,510 --> 00:24:42,970
Pretty Girl, I can take care of it.

331
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:03,160
How did you know I was here?

332
00:25:03,160 --> 00:25:05,678
Because I know you.

333
00:25:19,210 --> 00:25:21,440
Hai Yi?

334
00:25:23,750 --> 00:25:25,980
Hai Yi.

335
00:25:27,160 --> 00:25:29,070
Hai Yi?

336
00:25:29,070 --> 00:25:31,670
- Hai Yi—
- Leave me alone.

337
00:25:31,670 --> 00:25:35,109
Why are you here? You just ruined my drinking time.

338
00:25:35,110 --> 00:25:37,489
I don't want to fight anymore.

339
00:25:37,489 --> 00:25:40,090
Come, come home with me.

340
00:25:44,100 --> 00:25:45,500
"Home"?

341
00:25:48,890 --> 00:25:51,060
I don't have one.

342
00:25:53,020 --> 00:25:56,279
My dad is gone, and you don't care about me.

343
00:25:56,280 --> 00:26:00,330
Everyone leaves me. It's okay. I don't care.

344
00:26:00,330 --> 00:26:02,460
It's not the first time anyway.

345
00:26:02,460 --> 00:26:05,790
- Hai Yi.
- Don't touch me.

346
00:26:06,430 --> 00:26:08,310
- Leave me alone.
- Hai Yi.

347
00:26:08,310 --> 00:26:11,039
Scram. Scram...

348
00:26:11,040 --> 00:26:13,909
I don't want your pity. Scram...

349
00:26:13,910 --> 00:26:15,959
- Okay. I'll go.
- Scram!

350
00:26:15,960 --> 00:26:17,859
Scram!

351
00:26:17,859 --> 00:26:21,090
I'll go, but not now.

352
00:26:21,090 --> 00:26:22,840
Go away.

353
00:26:48,790 --> 00:26:50,939
Do you seriously want me to leave?

354
00:26:50,940 --> 00:26:53,189
You've annoyed me so much.

355
00:26:53,190 --> 00:26:56,729
I don't know what I want from you. Can you stop asking?

356
00:26:56,730 --> 00:26:58,020
I see.

357
00:26:58,020 --> 00:27:00,969
I'll resign and move out as soon as possible.

358
00:27:00,970 --> 00:27:03,729
I'll stay away from you and never show up again.

359
00:27:03,730 --> 00:27:05,919
That's not what I meant. Dai Zhe-ni!

360
00:27:05,920 --> 00:27:07,490
Never mind.

361
00:27:11,210 --> 00:27:14,479
I'll find a way to go back to my world,

362
00:27:14,480 --> 00:27:17,060
so that you won't be annoyed anymore.

363
00:27:28,920 --> 00:27:32,450
Dai Zhe-ni.

364
00:27:33,080 --> 00:27:34,930
Dai Zhe-ni.

365
00:27:38,930 --> 00:27:43,850
Don't go. I'm begging you.

366
00:27:43,850 --> 00:27:46,079
You just said I was annoying.

367
00:27:46,080 --> 00:27:49,730
I'm sorry. It's me...

368
00:27:54,830 --> 00:27:56,530
I'm sorry.

369
00:28:14,330 --> 00:28:18,960
I said you are annoying because you've confused me.

370
00:28:21,560 --> 00:28:23,280
I don't know what I want from you,

371
00:28:23,280 --> 00:28:26,390
because I like you no matter what you do.

372
00:28:34,380 --> 00:28:36,390
Are you drunk?

373
00:28:36,390 --> 00:28:39,530
I've never been more sober.

374
00:28:42,420 --> 00:28:44,080
Dai Zhe-ni...

375
00:28:45,990 --> 00:28:48,810
I don't care why you are here,

376
00:28:48,810 --> 00:28:51,020
or what brought you here.

377
00:28:54,040 --> 00:28:56,640
I just want to be with you.

378
00:28:58,790 --> 00:29:02,130
Live together. Work together.

379
00:29:05,530 --> 00:29:07,890
♫ The sceneries outside are stacked into shadows ♫

380
00:29:07,890 --> 00:29:11,980
♫ Longing becomes an illness, the senses are numbed ♫

381
00:29:11,980 --> 00:29:14,360
♫ Engraved in memory, every single drop ♫

382
00:29:14,360 --> 00:29:18,050
♫ I overestimate myself to provoke you ♫

383
00:29:18,050 --> 00:29:21,240
♫ I’ve used all my efforts to love in this life ♫

384
00:29:21,240 --> 00:29:27,140
♫ Please let me be a fish in my next life ♫

385
00:29:27,140 --> 00:29:33,170
♫ Always have a seven-second memory ♫

386
00:29:36,750 --> 00:29:41,910
This is... probably why I'm here.

387
00:30:23,830 --> 00:30:25,510
You knew?

388
00:30:26,120 --> 00:30:28,070
You did, too?

389
00:30:32,180 --> 00:30:35,020
I knew it when you mentioned stinky tofu.

390
00:30:35,020 --> 00:30:37,459
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

391
00:30:37,460 --> 00:30:40,089
You are so annoying. You always keep things from me.

392
00:30:40,090 --> 00:30:42,680
What else have you kept from me?

393
00:30:43,340 --> 00:30:45,099
Because...

394
00:30:45,099 --> 00:30:49,970
I didn't want you to feel sorry for that little boy and choose to stay.

395
00:30:49,970 --> 00:30:51,520
Silly.

396
00:30:52,200 --> 00:30:56,860
If I choose to stay, of course it's because—

397
00:30:56,860 --> 00:31:00,750
♫ You are everywhere on my mind ♫

398
00:31:00,750 --> 00:31:04,580
♫ Longing is suffocating me ♫

399
00:31:06,150 --> 00:31:08,120
I'm in love with you.

400
00:31:08,800 --> 00:31:11,410
I don't want you to say it first.

401
00:31:12,310 --> 00:31:16,160
♫ You are everywhere in this world ♫

402
00:31:16,160 --> 00:31:19,110
♫ My heart is threatened by loneliness ♫

403
00:31:19,110 --> 00:31:25,220
♫ But I can do nothing ♫

404
00:31:25,220 --> 00:31:30,040
♫ I tell myself to give up ♫

405
00:31:44,660 --> 00:31:48,600
♫ Driving on a sleepless raining night ♫

406
00:31:48,600 --> 00:31:51,510
♫ Aimlessly driving ♫

407
00:31:51,510 --> 00:31:53,380
Let's go to my place.

408
00:31:57,210 --> 00:32:01,469
I think I'll stay in the warehouse for now.

409
00:32:01,470 --> 00:32:05,469
Why? I have many rooms. It's more comfortable.

410
00:32:06,260 --> 00:32:07,659
It's not good.

411
00:32:07,660 --> 00:32:08,989
Why not?

412
00:32:08,990 --> 00:32:12,650
We lived together for so long before.

413
00:32:14,020 --> 00:32:16,419
When we were junior staff,

414
00:32:16,420 --> 00:32:18,810
no one cared about us.

415
00:32:18,810 --> 00:32:21,609
But now you are the chairman.

416
00:32:21,610 --> 00:32:23,820
You have just begun.

417
00:32:24,710 --> 00:32:27,010
Gossip is a fearful thing.

418
00:33:04,820 --> 00:33:06,530
[To: Lin Huai-en]

419
00:33:35,260 --> 00:33:36,519
"It's autumn now."

420
00:33:36,519 --> 00:33:38,089
"Day and night temperatures vary greatly."

421
00:33:38,090 --> 00:33:41,710
"Don't get sick. From Liang Wun-sen."

422
00:34:10,530 --> 00:34:12,490
Managing Director.

423
00:34:14,460 --> 00:34:16,490
I love you very much,

424
00:34:17,880 --> 00:34:21,630
but I don't think I can watch you hurt my benefactor.

425
00:34:39,080 --> 00:34:41,677
"Sir, breakfast is ready."

426
00:34:41,677 --> 00:34:43,169
"Something urgent came up at my hometown."

427
00:34:43,170 --> 00:34:45,043
"I need to take one month's leave."

428
00:34:45,043 --> 00:34:46,444
"Sorry for the short notice."

429
00:34:46,444 --> 00:34:49,306
"Please forgive me."

430
00:35:01,140 --> 00:35:04,440
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

431
00:35:04,440 --> 00:35:07,426
- What are you doing?
- I'm having breakfast.

432
00:35:07,426 --> 00:35:08,908
What about you?

433
00:35:08,908 --> 00:35:11,950
I am too. Look.

434
00:35:16,480 --> 00:35:18,870
It looks so much.

435
00:35:18,870 --> 00:35:22,160
Yes. How about you? What are you having?

436
00:35:29,450 --> 00:35:30,970
Don't eat that.

437
00:35:30,970 --> 00:35:33,790
I'll bring some of these to the company for you.

438
00:35:34,690 --> 00:35:37,540
You only think of me when you can't finish them.

439
00:35:37,540 --> 00:35:41,730
I save them specially for you. Forget it then.

440
00:35:41,730 --> 00:35:45,040
I'll eat. I'll eat.

441
00:35:45,040 --> 00:35:48,710
I'll take anything as long as it's edible.

442
00:35:49,620 --> 00:35:52,230
All right. See you later.

443
00:35:52,230 --> 00:35:54,150
See you later.

444
00:35:54,150 --> 00:35:56,010
You hang up first.

445
00:35:56,010 --> 00:35:59,970
- You hang up first.
- You hang up first.

446
00:35:59,970 --> 00:36:02,650
All right. See you.

447
00:36:02,650 --> 00:36:04,380
Bye.

448
00:36:16,640 --> 00:36:20,279
[About Ho-Lee Jin-hua, it's all done. Don't worry.]

449
00:36:25,030 --> 00:36:29,480
Grandma, I hope you like your new home.

450
00:36:47,530 --> 00:36:49,389
Although we don't live together,

451
00:36:49,390 --> 00:36:51,969
we get to work together again.

452
00:36:51,970 --> 00:36:53,700
Happy.

453
00:37:07,890 --> 00:37:09,239
Managing Director.

454
00:37:09,240 --> 00:37:13,170
This is Lin Huai-en's application for transferring to another department.

455
00:37:20,030 --> 00:37:23,550
Managing Director, I swear I didn't do anything.

456
00:37:23,550 --> 00:37:28,090
I did not force him to change departments.

457
00:37:28,090 --> 00:37:31,810
Don't worry. I trust you.

458
00:37:33,720 --> 00:37:38,190
Should I reject the request?

459
00:37:47,140 --> 00:37:49,080
Let him be.

460
00:38:00,490 --> 00:38:02,720
It's my pleasure to develop

461
00:38:02,720 --> 00:38:05,590
a brand new business model in Australia.

462
00:38:05,600 --> 00:38:09,340
Thank you all for your support for Poseidon

463
00:38:09,340 --> 00:38:11,421
since my dad passed away.

464
00:38:11,421 --> 00:38:14,439
Sure. We are very excited about this project in the future.

465
00:38:14,439 --> 00:38:16,359
Yi, I'm sorry for your loss.

466
00:38:16,360 --> 00:38:18,230
I'm sorry.

467
00:38:30,040 --> 00:38:34,140
Chairman. Shall we have lunch together?

468
00:39:38,650 --> 00:39:40,970
Let's go on a date tonight.

469
00:39:42,930 --> 00:39:44,480
Sure.

470
00:39:52,450 --> 00:39:56,330
I couldn't even talk to you at the office.

471
00:39:56,330 --> 00:39:58,120
Sorry.

472
00:39:58,120 --> 00:40:01,570
Come on. You have so much to handle.

473
00:40:01,570 --> 00:40:05,100
I'm glad I can help you by being by your side.

474
00:40:05,780 --> 00:40:07,680
Thank you.

475
00:40:12,830 --> 00:40:16,340
It's tiring running a company.

476
00:40:17,760 --> 00:40:21,070
I've finally got to understand how my father felt.

477
00:40:28,520 --> 00:40:30,160
Dai Zhe-ni...

478
00:40:31,280 --> 00:40:34,270
This was where we first met.

479
00:40:35,000 --> 00:40:37,080
Do you remember?

480
00:40:37,080 --> 00:40:39,170
Of course, I do.

481
00:40:39,170 --> 00:40:42,430
I still can't believe this.

482
00:40:42,430 --> 00:40:45,490
You were that Big Brother back then.

483
00:40:46,290 --> 00:40:48,780
I feel the same.

484
00:40:48,780 --> 00:40:53,800
You were so cute when you were little, but now...

485
00:40:56,060 --> 00:40:58,790
What? I've become a hot guy, right?

486
00:40:58,790 --> 00:41:01,060
And you love me so much.

487
00:41:01,060 --> 00:41:03,670
Why did you have to say it out loud?

488
00:41:03,670 --> 00:41:07,760
Right, right, right... You've become a hot guy, okay?

489
00:41:14,470 --> 00:41:16,500
Growing up,

490
00:41:17,870 --> 00:41:20,670
whenever I felt lonely,

491
00:41:22,850 --> 00:41:26,300
I always made a wish in front of the lucky bracelet.

492
00:41:28,100 --> 00:41:30,660
I wished to see you again.

493
00:41:33,080 --> 00:41:36,045
I didn't expect it would come true.

494
00:41:42,480 --> 00:41:47,140
It's like God has taken my dad away,

495
00:41:48,700 --> 00:41:51,910
but He sends you here to protect me.

496
00:42:11,790 --> 00:42:16,260
Yes. What a magical fate.

497
00:42:16,260 --> 00:42:21,310
But... What about my grandma?

498
00:42:34,980 --> 00:42:36,720
Come in.

499
00:42:39,820 --> 00:42:43,600
Hello, Executive Assistant Dai. I'm your assistant. It's my first day today.

500
00:42:43,600 --> 00:42:45,020
Lin Huai-en!

501
00:42:45,020 --> 00:42:47,070
I'm your assistant from today onward.

502
00:42:47,070 --> 00:42:49,790
- I look forward to learning from you.
- Seriously?

503
00:42:49,790 --> 00:42:52,299
I even have an assistant!

504
00:42:52,299 --> 00:42:55,480
Chairman sent me to help you.

505
00:42:55,480 --> 00:42:57,089
See? Chairman is very nice to you.

506
00:42:57,090 --> 00:42:59,200
He doesn't want you to be too tired.

507
00:43:00,860 --> 00:43:04,190
We can work together from now on.

508
00:43:04,190 --> 00:43:05,279
Yes.

509
00:43:05,280 --> 00:43:07,310
Awesome!

510
00:43:07,980 --> 00:43:09,420
- Hello, Executive Assistant.
- Good morning.

511
00:43:09,420 --> 00:43:11,310
- Good morning.
- Hello, Executive Assistant.

512
00:43:11,310 --> 00:43:13,070
All the best.

513
00:43:13,070 --> 00:43:15,280
Hello, Executive Assistant.

514
00:43:25,000 --> 00:43:27,130
Executive Assistant, I'll refill it for you.

515
00:43:28,120 --> 00:43:29,659
Executive Assistant, I'll print it for you.

516
00:43:29,660 --> 00:43:31,359
Ten copies of each document.

517
00:43:31,360 --> 00:43:32,870
All right.

518
00:43:36,270 --> 00:43:38,670
